Package org.bluezoo.gumdrop.http.h2

Interface H2FrameHandler

All Known Implementing Classes:
FileHTTPConnection, HTTPClientConnection, HTTPConnection, PriorityAwareHTTPConnection, ServletConnection
public interface H2FrameHandler
Callback interface for receiving parsed HTTP/2 frames.

Implementations receive frame data directly from an H2Parser without intermediate Frame object allocation. Both server-side (HTTPConnection) and client-side (HTTPClientConnection) connections implement this interface.

Each frame type has a dedicated callback method with the parsed fields as parameters. ByteBuffer parameters are slices of the parser's input buffer and should be consumed or copied before returning.

Author:
Chris Burdess

  • Method Details

    • dataFrameReceived

      void dataFrameReceived(int streamId, boolean endStream, ByteBuffer data)
      Called when a DATA frame is received.
      Parameters:
      streamId - the stream identifier
      endStream - true if this is the last frame for the stream
      data - the data payload (a slice - consume or copy before returning)

    • headersFrameReceived

      void headersFrameReceived(int streamId, boolean endStream, boolean endHeaders, int streamDependency, boolean exclusive, int weight, ByteBuffer headerBlockFragment)
      Called when a HEADERS frame is received.
      Parameters:
      streamId - the stream identifier
      endStream - true if this is the last frame for the stream
      endHeaders - true if this completes the header block
      streamDependency - the stream dependency (0 if no priority)
      exclusive - true for exclusive stream dependency
      weight - the priority weight (1-256, only valid if streamDependency > 0)
      headerBlockFragment - the HPACK-encoded header block (a slice)

    • priorityFrameReceived

      void priorityFrameReceived(int streamId, int streamDependency, boolean exclusive, int weight)
      Called when a PRIORITY frame is received.
      Parameters:
      streamId - the stream identifier
      streamDependency - the stream this one depends on
      exclusive - true for exclusive dependency
      weight - the priority weight (1-256)

    • rstStreamFrameReceived

      void rstStreamFrameReceived(int streamId, int errorCode)
      Called when a RST_STREAM frame is received.
      Parameters:
      streamId - the stream identifier
      errorCode - the error code indicating why the stream is being terminated

    • settingsFrameReceived

      void settingsFrameReceived(boolean ack, Map<Integer,Integer> settings)
      Called when a SETTINGS frame is received.
      Parameters:
      ack - true if this is an acknowledgement of our SETTINGS
      settings - map of setting identifier to value (empty if ack is true)

    • pushPromiseFrameReceived

      void pushPromiseFrameReceived(int streamId, int promisedStreamId, boolean endHeaders, ByteBuffer headerBlockFragment)
      Called when a PUSH_PROMISE frame is received.
      Parameters:
      streamId - the stream identifier of the associated request
      promisedStreamId - the stream identifier for the pushed response
      endHeaders - true if this completes the header block
      headerBlockFragment - the HPACK-encoded header block (a slice)

    • pingFrameReceived

      void pingFrameReceived(boolean ack, long opaqueData)
      Called when a PING frame is received.
      Parameters:
      ack - true if this is a PING response
      opaqueData - the 8 bytes of opaque data

    • goawayFrameReceived

      void goawayFrameReceived(int lastStreamId, int errorCode, ByteBuffer debugData)
      Called when a GOAWAY frame is received.
      Parameters:
      lastStreamId - the highest stream ID the sender will accept
      errorCode - the error code indicating why the connection is closing
      debugData - optional debug information (a slice, may be empty)

    • windowUpdateFrameReceived

      void windowUpdateFrameReceived(int streamId, int windowSizeIncrement)
      Called when a WINDOW_UPDATE frame is received.
      Parameters:
      streamId - the stream identifier (0 for connection-level)
      windowSizeIncrement - the number of bytes to add to the window

    • continuationFrameReceived

      void continuationFrameReceived(int streamId, boolean endHeaders, ByteBuffer headerBlockFragment)
      Called when a CONTINUATION frame is received.
      Parameters:
      streamId - the stream identifier
      endHeaders - true if this completes the header block
      headerBlockFragment - the HPACK-encoded header block (a slice)

    • frameError

      void frameError(int errorCode, int streamId, String message)
      Called when a protocol error is detected during frame parsing.
      Parameters:
      errorCode - the HTTP/2 error code
      streamId - the stream ID where the error occurred (0 for connection-level)
      message - a human-readable description of the error

    • typeToString

      static String typeToString(int type)
      Returns a human-readable name for a frame type.
      Parameters:
      type - the frame type constant
      Returns:
      the type name (e.g., "DATA", "HEADERS", etc.)

      Returns a human-readable name for an error code.

      errorCode - the error code constant
      Returns:
